title: In the Fortress of the Wizard
The Crystal Book
description: Grubby, Teddy, Gimmick, and Fuzz the fob find the crystals have a way to identify a characteristic of whoever is holding one. Gimmick is described as "inventive", which sends him on an inventing spree. At the same time, Tweeg, Eleanor (Tweeg's mother), and L.B. head back to Tweeg's Tower, and then Eleanor and L.B. send Tweeg to attempt to steal from the three in the valley. Teddy, Grubby, and Gimmick use a crystal to bamboozle Tweeg.

title: Teddy and the Mudblups
description: Gimmick want to try out a new invention, so the three fly out to the Great Desert. To cause general mayhem, Tweeg, L.B., and Eleanor follow. All six end up becoming prisoners of the Mudblups. However, the king of the Mudblups falls head over heels for Eleanor, who does not return the affection. To get out, Tweeg puts on a dress and pretends to be Eleanor, saying "she" will marry the king if he'll let Tweeg and L.B. go, with a chest full of gems, of course. Tweeg and L.B. get away scot free, while Eleanor is dragged away for marriage. The Trio impersonate Mudblups for their own escape by covering themselves in mud.

title: Win One for the Twipper
description: Tweeg challenges the Trio to a Grungeball game and gets Gimmick to bet their house. Tweeg's team is a bunch of ringers--sunglass-wearing Mudblups--to play against the Trio and the Surf Grunges. However, Tweeg and L.B. give the Grunges hot dogs made from poisonous weeds and make them all sick. It's up to Gimmick, Grubby, and Teddy to save the day for the Grunge All-Stars...which of course they do. Grudgingly, Tweeg hands over Gimmick's prize, which was promised to be the chest of gems, but is really just filled with coal.

title: Tweeg Joins M.A.V.O.
description: The Wooly-What's-It drops in on the Trio, and they show him Gimmick's "All About Fobs" book and the Crystal book belonging to Teddy. Unfortunately, Tweeg, who's about to be initiated into M.A.V.O., just happens to be eavesdropping. When the four head up to the loft, Tweeg sneaks in and swipes the book left on the coffee table. When the Trio and Wooly discover the theft, they (correctly) guess Tweeg must have stolen it. Teddy is revved up to get it back from M.A.V.O., but strangely, Gimmick isn't as excited. Tweeg is congratulated by Quellor, head of M.A.V.O., for bringing him the book. During all this, the four sneak in, posing as caterers. They swipe back the book and run off. Tweeg and L.B. are throw in the dungeon. Once they get back to the house, Teddy wonders why Gimmick didn't care that M.A.V.O. had the Crystal book, but Gimmick explains that Tweeg had actually stolen his fob book instead, and not Teddy's book.

title: The Mushroom Forest
description: While visiting the Mushroom Forest, the Trio meet a group of very shy shape-shifters, who call themselves the "Nothings." Teddy persuades them to call themselves "Anythings" as they can become anything they want. While they're gone, Quellor sends the Gutang to ransack the house. They find the plans to Gimmick's Airship and sell them to Quellor.

title: Something in the Soup
description: The Jungle Grunges need help when their oversized vegetables start to disappear. Gimmick tries to set a trap, but gets caught in it himself. The thieves are uncovered as the Anythings, who were excited about their new name and status, and didn't realize they were stealing from the Grunges. Some Anythings are disguised as vegetables and are almost cut up to be part of Grunge Gumbo, but are saved in the last few seconds. While this is happening, Quellor and M.A.V.O. have unveiled their own Airship, dubbed the "Eclipse", and set out to find Teddy, the gang, and the elusive Crystals.
